## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Set required secrets (POSTGRES_PASSWORD and JWT_SECRET are mandatory)
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — at minimum set POSTGRES_PASSWORD and JWT_SECRET

# 2. Start all services (backend + frontend + database)
docker-compose up --build

# Or use Make
make dev
```

The service will be available at:
- **Frontend (Next.js):** http://localhost:3000
- **API:** http://localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}
{% if language == 'python-fastapi' %}
- **Swagger UI:** http://localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}/docs
{% endif %}
- **Health:** http://localhost:{{ port | default('8000') }}/health

For the mobile app (separate from Docker):
```bash
cd mobile
npm install
npx expo start
```

